CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 8, 1944, pg. 13, reads: "Hoofologists - Paul White and Teddy Hale are the two whirlwind dancers whom Ted Lewis features with his show, which is currently swinging on the theatre circuit. Paul and Teddy provide several of the high spots in the revue when they come with their skits with the high-hatted maestro. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dancers Paul White and Teddy Hale wearing cravats and tap shoes, posed reaching towards each other backstage at Stanley Theatre
